#
# Pre-commit hook: enforce repository-level commit-hygiene lints.
#
# This hook is tracked in the repo (.githooks/pre-commit) and activated
# via `make install-hooks`, which sets core.hooksPath to .githooks. One
# command per clone; updates to this file propagate on `git pull`.
#
# Each lint is a standalone script in tools/. Add new lints here as they
# land. Any nonzero exit fails the commit.
#
# Lints in order:
#   check-banned-paths:        Paths deleted from git must not reappear on
#                              disk. See tools/banned-paths.txt and
#                              tools/check-banned-paths.py.
#   check-index-isolation:     STATUS.md structural changes must commit
#                              alone (or with docs-only siblings), never
#                              bundled with *.rs source files. See
#                              tools/check-index-isolation.py for rationale.
#   check-lockfile-additions:  When Cargo.lock is staged, surface every
#                              new (crate, version) pair so the human
#                              reviews supply-chain deltas before they
#                              land. Advisory only — exit 0 unconditional.
#                              T-1 in docs/threat-model.md.
#   check-unsafe-coverage:     Every `unsafe { ... }` block must carry a
#                              `// SAFETY:` comment in its preceding
#                              comment block (CLAUDE.md Development
#                              Convention 1). Don't-grow-the-baseline
#                              gate. Tier 1 E3 (prancy-manatee plan).
#
# Bypass: `git commit --no-verify` (discouraged; use for emergencies only).

set -e

cd "$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)"

python3 tools/check-banned-paths.py
python3 tools/check-index-isolation.py
python3 tools/check-lockfile-additions.py
python3 tools/check-unsafe-coverage.py
